OL,3,CCustomer anger at 'exorbitant'
OL,4,Ccommunal heating
OL,6,FTens of thousands of households on
OL,7,Fcommunal heat systems are not
OL,8,Fprotected by the usual energy price
OL,9,Fcap - and some customers say new
OL,10,Fgovernment regulations still leave
OL,11,Fthem out in the cold.
OL,13,FWe spoke to Jakia Begum whose flat is
OL,14,Fconnected to a shared heating system.
OL,16,F"In 2023 it jumped from #42 to #88 a
OL,17,Fweek," she told us. "Whether you have
OL,18,Fmoney or not, you still have to pay
OL,19,Ffor heating.
