OL,3,CCustomer anger at 'exorbitant'
OL,4,Ccommunal heating
OL,6,FThe energy minister has described
OL,7,Fthose increases as "exorbitant".
OL,9,FNow for the first time Ofgem, the
OL,10,Fofficial energy watchdog, is
OL,11,Fregulating heat networks - but its
OL,12,Ffull set of rules don't come in until
OL,13,F2027.
OL,15,FMany believe customers on communal
OL,16,Fsystems need special protection
OL,17,Fbecause they can't choose who supplies
OL,18,Ftheir energy - or switch to a better
OL,19,Fdeal.
