OL,3,CCustomer anger at 'exorbitant'
OL,4,Ccommunal heating
OL,6,FThe government wants to esculate
OL,7,Fshared heating schemes, recently
OL,8,Fallocating #47m. Despite its new
OL,9,Frules, there will still be no price
OL,10,Fcap for these households - something
OL,11,Fthe government says would be too
OL,12,Fcomplex.
OL,14,FThe Energy Minister, Martin McClusky
OL,15,FMP told ITV News: "A price cap isn't
OL,16,Fpossible, but this will make sure that
OL,17,Fthere aren't the kind of unscrupulous
OL,18,Fprice increases we have seen from some
OL,19,Fheat works for the last few years;
OL,20,Fthat we don't end up with these
OL,21,Fextremes of pricing that we've had."
